com.digi.xbee.api.packet.ip

Class TXIPv4Packet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeePacket
      • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeeAPIPacket
        • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.ip.TXIPv4Packet

  • public class TXIPv4Packet
extends XBeeAPIPacket
    This class represents a TX (Transmit) IPv4 packet. Packet is built using the parameters of the constructor or providing a valid API payload.
    Since:
    1.2.0
    See Also:
    RXIPv4Packet, XBeeAPIPacket

    • Constructor Detail

      • TXIPv4Packet

        public TXIPv4Packet(int frameID,
                    Inet4Address destAddress,
                    int destPort,
                    int sourcePort,
                    IPProtocol protocol,
                    int transmitOptions,
                    byte[] data)
        Class constructor. Instantiates a new TXIPv4Packet object with the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        frameID - Frame ID.
        destAddress - IP address of the destination device.
        destPort - Destination port number.
        sourcePort - Source port number.
        protocol - Protocol used for transmitted data.
        transmitOptions - Transmit options bitfield. Can be OPTIONS_LEAVE_SOCKET_OPEN or OPTIONS_CLOSE_SOCKET.
        data - Transmit data bytes.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if frameID < 0 or if frameID > 255 or if destPort < 0 or if destPort > 65535 or if sourcePort < 0 or if sourcePort > 65535 or if transmitOptions are invalid.
        NullPointerException - if destAddress == null or if protocol == null.
        See Also:
        IPProtocol, Inet4Address

      • createPacket

        public static TXIPv4Packet createPacket(byte[] payload)
        Creates a new TXIPv4Packet object from the given payload.
        Parameters:
        payload - The API frame payload. It must start with the frame type corresponding to a TX IPv4 packet (0x20). The byte array must be in OperatingMode.API mode.
        Returns:
        Parsed TX IPv4 packet.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if payload[0] != APIFrameType.TX_IPV4.getValue() or if payload.length < .
        NullPointerException - if payload == null.
